Listen up, you pirate wannabes!
These waters are under Felder's
protectionâ€”and you damn well
know what that means!
8:
Hah! Try us, princess. Felder's
washed up, and we all know it!
25:
Reticia, that was a risky move, even
for a seasoned fighter.
28:
You need to keep your wits in check.
Or else... one of these days, you'll
bite off more trouble than you can
chew.
31:
Gee, thanks, Mom.
...I already know I'm too gutsy.
34: But I... I can't sit back and do nothing!
40: I have to draw faster! Shoot sharper!
44:
*pant* Hahhh, I'm pushing myself
too hard again, huh?
49:
Reticia? Sorry, have you seen
Nimbus?
53:
You just missed him. Dunno where
he went though. Want me to help
look?
56:
Oh, no, it's fine. I can just carry the
grocery bags by myself.
63:
You're a life saver! I was afraid I
wouldn't make it in time for the sale.
66:
No problem. I was done training
anyways, so it's not like I had
anything else to do.
70:
I'm amazed you manage to find
time to train every day. Don't you
have mountains of paperwork too?
73:
I'm used to it. Besides, you do all the
chores, and YOU still find time to
practice.
76:
Mmm, I think it's more that... I dunno.
I get worried that I don't train
enough.
84:
I'm nowhere near as good as the
others, so I have to work twice as
hard, or I'll never catch up.
91:
Well, I'm the YOUNGER sister, right?
Lucretia was supposed to be the
next head arbiter.
94:
But years back, when Zegra
vanished, things got... rough.
96:
Our parents did everything they
could to prevent it, but there was a
huge battle and... they never made
it home.
98:
Lucretia survived, but only barely.
Even now, her injuries prevent her
from handling much beyond the
bureaucratic side of arbiter work.
102:
I'm the only one who can fight, but...
I'm a sorry excuse for a Felder.
109:
It's fine. I swore that I'd train
harderâ€”for their sakes.
111:
I'm Reticia, heir to House Felderâ€”and
I'm gonna act like it!
115: I won't let ANYONE disturb the seas!
119:
Then you REALLY can't afford to fight
so recklessly. If something
happened to you...
124:
I-I know that! I justâ€”I get caught up
in the moment.
127:
I've been trying not to overwork
myself, but... *sigh*
131:
At the very least, you don't have to
be "Lady Felder" around us.
134:
I'm sure there's lots of pressure on
you back home, but...
137:
This is Palpebra. You're just a normal
girl as far as anyone here knows.
146:
Why should I care?! Who do you
think you are?!
147:
Who do you think YOU are?! You're
the one who bumped into ME!
150:
You there! By order of House Felder,
cease and desist!
161:
Am I supposed to've heard of you?
Stay out of this, kid!
167:
Have a look around you. You're
scaring people.
169:
This little fight isn't gonna do your
reputations any favors.
172:
If you can't reconcile your
differences peacefully, I can be your
witness for a proper duel.
175: A duel?! It's not THAT big of a deal...
178:
Hmm. Then how about you both
take a deep breath, explain your
grievances... and then I'll help
mediate. Okay?
183:
You had that fight settled in
seconds. You really ARE a pro.
187:
Stop. I just rushed in without
thinking, and you know it.
190:
But, um. I guess I did okay, even
without the Felder name to rely on.
196:
I didn't do anything. I should be
thanking YOU for all the help.
198:
Besides, it was fun getting to know
you better.
204: It was nice talking to you too!
233:
Wh-wh-what WAS that?! Why do I
feel so...
